xanadu may refer to :    xanadu , china or shangdu , the summer capital of kublai khan 's yuan empire   " kubla khan " , a poem by samuel taylor coleridge , which popularised the name xanadu for shangdu    places    xi'an , china , formerly chang'an , which was often the dynastic capital from the han to tang dynasties .

